result.text:
Statins reduce dementia risk by up to 63%

Published earlier this year, the largest meta-analysis to date involved over 7 million participants in 55 studies and concluded that statin use reduced the risk of Alzheimer Disease and Dementia.

0/ Being exposed to statins for over 3 years reduced dementia risk by 63%

1/ Statin users in general demonstrated 14% reduction in overall dementia risk, 18% and 11% reduction in Alzheimer Disease and Vascular Dementia risk, respectively.

2/ Subgroup analysis showed that statins reduced dementia risk in type-2-diabetics by 13%.

3/ Rosuvastatin use correlated with the greatest dementia risk reduction of 28%

4/ Caution: statins are prescription drugs and should not be taken without consulting your doctors. While common side effects include muscle pain, a much rarer side effect is muscles breaking down (Rhabdomoylysis) which leads to severe muscle pain, and irreversible muscle and kidney damage with continued use of statins.

legacy.full_text: Solana smart contract architecture tip: instead of tying a pda or authority to a wallet, instead tie it to an NFT you mint into that wallet. Verify authority by ownership of the NFT. Now users can see they have this ability by looking in their wallet, and can conveniently move it

NFTs as Authorities

I think about this tweet all the time, and it's something I thought about when we added Execute to @Metaplex Core.

NFTs as Authorities make it possible to transfer, trade, or burn permissions. And doing this has never been easier.
